# Spotlight news — GNews (https://gnews.io). Get a free key at
# https://gnews.io/register. No key anywhere → the Spotlight renders the
# bundled mock data (no network request).

# ── Production (Vercel) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Server-only key used by the serverless proxy (api/news.js). NO "VITE_" prefix,
# so it is never exposed to the browser bundle. Set this in the Vercel project's
# Environment Variables (Production scope), then redeploy.
#   GNEWS_API_KEY=your_key_here
#
# GNews's free tier blocks browser (CORS) requests from non-localhost origins,
# which is why production goes through the proxy instead of calling GNews directly.

# ── Local development (bun run dev / vite) ───────────────────────────────────
# Client-side key used ONLY in dev, where GNews allows localhost browser calls.
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (git-ignored) and set:
VITE_GNEWS_API_KEY=

# Optional overrides (defaults shown) — apply to the proxy via GNEWS_* and to
# dev via VITE_GNEWS_*:
# GNEWS_CATEGORY=business
# GNEWS_LANG=en
# VITE_GNEWS_CATEGORY=business
# VITE_GNEWS_LANG=en

# Force mock data even when a key is present (handy for offline/demo):
# VITE_USE_MOCK_NEWS=true
